Commit: 88bc91ba3b3cf4a077604097d387f1c938f9637d&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="136581" author="kit.westneat" created="Wed, 16 Dec 2015 17:18:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for getting this together Chris, it&apos;s way better than anything I would have written. I uploaded it to gerrit and added some comments and suggestions. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, there&apos;s at least one place in the manual that references the need to have client UIDs and GIDs matched on the MDS. Ideally these would mention nodemap now. Here&apos;s the one I saw:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml#section_rh2_d4w_gk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml#section_rh2_d4w_gk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="136554" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 16 Dec 2015 16:19:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Kit Westneat (kit.westneat@gmail.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/17634&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/17634&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-314&quot; title=&quot;Create additions to the Lustre manual for IU&amp;#39;s nodemap feature.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-314&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-314&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; nodemap: first commit of nodemap documentation&lt;br/&gt;
Project: doc/manual&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: f522a4b1a3edabf75859760e7f2237c762187249&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135714" author="rhenwood" created="Wed, 9 Dec 2015 20:42:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve checked and the HPDD auth provider does not allow anyone other than HPDD employees to authenticate against Gerrit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You must use a Google account, a Yahoo account, or an other OpenID provider to log into Gerrit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135712" author="hannac" created="Wed, 9 Dec 2015 20:21:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks.  I used HPDD auth (&lt;a href=&quot;https://id.hpdd.intel.com/openidserver/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://id.hpdd.intel.com/openidserver/&lt;/a&gt;).  Perhaps that isn&apos;t what I think it is.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached both files.  LustreNodemap.xml is brand new, and the only change to III_LustreAdministration was to add a line for the new file.  Any feedback is welcome.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The git commit was to be:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-314&quot; title=&quot;Create additions to the Lustre manual for IU&amp;#39;s nodemap feature.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-314&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-314&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Additions for Lustre manual for nodemap feature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added a chapter in the Lustre manual to describe the&lt;br/&gt;
nodemap &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3291&quot; title=&quot;IU UID/GID Mapping Feature&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3291&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3291&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; terminology, briefly demonstrate use&lt;br/&gt;
cases and setup, and describe potential pitfalls.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="135710" author="rhenwood" created="Wed, 9 Dec 2015 20:13:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, you can attached it here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m curious about your Gerrit issue: which auth provider do you use?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135706" author="hannac" created="Wed, 9 Dec 2015 20:03:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Richard,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I seem to be in a Gerrit rabbit-hole in which I cannot reset my password, and my current password does not work (although it works just fine here in HPDD Jira).  Can I attach the new LustreNodemap.xml file and one-line change to III_LustreAdministration.xml here for review?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135498" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 15:22:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Location sounds good, and outline sounds good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135495" author="hannac" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 15:09:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Richard,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The LU for the feature is 3291:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LU-3291&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.hpdd.intel.com/browse/LU-3291&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The feature is currently a technology preview in 2.7, with more landing in 2.8, but the documentation will reflect features up to 2.9.  I would edit the label to 2.9, but it doesn&apos;t seem I have the permissions to.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would a section in the operation manual heading III (Administering Lustre), between 22-23 be an appropriate location for this documentation?  It should include a description and example use case of the nodemap feature.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135493" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 14:56:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The ultimate destination is the Operations Manual:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.hpdd.intel.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135492" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 14:55:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for this Chris.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Can you add in a label for the Lustre version this feature will be present in?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, is there an LU ticket you can link to?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="135491" author="hannac" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 14:55:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been tasked with creating this documentation.  Do you have any suggestions as to where in the manual the documentation should land?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
